Sentencas: LaNbO4-NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) composites are prepared and investigated as an anode-support material for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Improved mechanical properties and thermal expansion behavior of NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 composite by addition of LaNbO4 for anode-support of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To tailor the coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE), electrical conductivity, fracture strength sigma and fracture toughness K-IC of the composite, various amounts of LaNbO4 from 0 to 30 wt.% are added into 53 wt.% NiO-47 wt.% YSZ composite.
Titulo: Improved mechanical properties and thermal expansion behavior of NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 composite by addition of LaNbO4 for anode-support of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With LaNbO4 addition into the NiO-YSZ, sigma changes insignificantly, whereas CTE decreases and K-IC increases monotonously.
Titulo: Improved mechanical properties and thermal expansion behavior of NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 composite by addition of LaNbO4 for anode-support of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For 30 wt.% LaNbO4-NiO-YSZ, the CTE is 12.4 x 10 (6) K (1) (250-1000 degrees C), which is much closer to that of YSZ, and the K-IC is 3.1 MPa-m(1/2), which is 42% increase compared with that of the NiO-YSZ.
Titulo: Improved mechanical properties and thermal expansion behavior of NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 composite by addition of LaNbO4 for anode-support of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The increase in fracture toughness is possibly due to the domain switch within LaNbO4 and the overall grain refinement of the composite.
Titulo: Improved mechanical properties and thermal expansion behavior of NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 composite by addition of LaNbO4 for anode-support of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the reduced composites decreases with increasing the amount of LaNbO4 and shows metallic conducting behavior with temperature.
Titulo: Improved mechanical properties and thermal expansion behavior of NiO-Y2O3 stabilized ZrO2 composite by addition of LaNbO4 for anode-support of planar solid oxide fuel cells
